<br>
As long as Holstic Crusaders are not on a planar rotation then any number (or as many as the raid leader wishes) can attend.  If Holistic Crusaders are in an alliance that does go on planar raids (VFA I think isnt it?) then your numbers will be very limited.  According to KGC rules on planar and large target raids, guests from other alliances and guilds that are planar capable are allowed, but only if they are not necessary to the success of the plane.<br>
<br>
That is, if the raid has no clerics or enchanters, then any cleric or enchanter must come from a non-planes capable guild.  Now these rules are somewhat flexible, however, it has always been KCoG policy to follow the KGC rules as much as possible.<br>
<br>
Of course, KCoG generally gets so many people that no single person is necessary to the success of the raid.  It is one reason I always took everyone who showed up.  That relieved me of the possibility of having to defend myself on the KGC boards for violating the rules.<br>
<br>
The long and short of it is, yes you are welcome so long as you are not vital to the success of the raid and are aware that should any cuts need to be made due to numbers, KCoG policy is to cut from the planes capable guilds first, even if you are a higher level than someone from a non-planes capable guild.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
The Watchmen<br>
